node.title: Here’s what to watch for in the House on Friday.
node.alt: A House vote on Friday would send the $1 trillion bipartisan infrastructure bill to President Biden for his signature.
node.description: If House Democrats succeed, they will pass two marquee pieces of legislation by day’s end, sending one bill to the president’s desk and the other to the Senate.
node.content: ["Democratic leaders in the House, aiming to break through an intraparty stalemate, are trying to hold key votes on President Biden\u2019s agenda on Friday. If they succeed, they will pass two marquee pieces of legislation by day\u2019s end, sending one bill to the president\u2019s desk and the other to the Senate.", "Here are three votes to watch as the day goes on."]
